For example, if the unique tiling is the checkerboard pattern where all horizontal dominoes are in even rows, then marking all cells in even rows would prevent vertical dominoes. But this requires marking 4 cells (each row has 4 cells, but if we mark every other cell in a row, that's 2 per row, total 8 cells). Not helpful. Alternatively, if the unique tiling is forced to be all horizontal dominoes, then marking all leftmost cells in each 2x2 block would prevent vertical dominoes. For a 4x4 board, this would require marking 4 cells (one in each 2x2 block's left column). Then, the tiling is forced to be all horizontal dominoes. Similarly, if the unique tiling is all vertical dominoes, mark the top cells in each 2x2 block. Therefore, in this case, k=4. But is there a way to do with fewer than 4 marked cells?
